Description: Fragment of flattened handle with a gradual curve from a pottery transport amphora. Accreted. Circular, button stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Mentaios. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0919.11. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0397)
